As noted in my [[Leopard set-up notes]], I couldn't get [[MySQL]] to build on [[Leopard]]Â 10.5.0, but I could with 10.5.1.

On upgrading to Rails 2.0RC2 (see "[[Upgrading to Rails 2.0RC2 on Mac OS X Leopard]]") I noticed that they'd added some instructions to the <tt>config/database.yml</tt> file for installing the mysql [[gem]] on Leopard:

<pre>sudo env ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386" gem install mysql -- --with-mysql-config=/usr/local/mysql/bin/mysql_config</pre>

Looks like this advice probably originated from [http://trac.macosforge.org/projects/ruby/wiki/Troubleshooting here].

But note, when I just did a plain <tt>./configure && make</tt> for MySQL, the <tt>mysql_config</tt> tool was ''not'' installed at that path, but at <tt>/usr/local/bin/mysql_config</tt> instead.

So, in my case, I had to do this (note the different value for <tt>--with-mysql-config</tt>):

<pre>$ sudo env ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386" gem install mysql -- --with-mysql-config=/usr/local/bin/mysql_config
